-* `limit` (Integer) / `window` (Number): emit at most `limit` calls per
-  `window` milliseconds (fixed window).
+* `limit` (Integer) / `window` (Number): token-bucket rate limiter. The
+  bucket has capacity `limit` and refills at `limit / window` tokens per
+  millisecond; it starts full. Every emitted log consumes one token, so
+  short bursts of up to `limit` calls go through immediately and sustained
+  traffic is paced smoothly — without the 2x-burst-at-boundary behaviour of
+  a naive fixed-window counter.
